                                      21 *TITLE:                                                                 00126021
                                      22 *                                                                       00132021
                                      23 *   'IKFCBL40'                                                          00138021
                                      24 *                                                                       00144021
                                      25 *STATUS:                                                                00150021
                                      26 *                                                                       00156021
                                      27 *   CHANGE LEVEL 000                                                    00162021
                                      28 *                                                                       00168021
                                      29 *FUNCTION/OPERATION:                                                    00174021
                                      30 *                                                                       00180021
                                      31 *   CHECKS SYNTAX OF PROCEDURE DIVISION. SUPPRESSES INCORRECT OUTPU     00186021
                                      32 *   REDUCES P1 TO P2 TEXT BY ELIMINATING NON-ESSENTIAL WORDS AND        00192021
                                      33 *   ATOMIZING EACH STATEMENT INTO A SERIES OF VERB STRINGS, I.E.,       00198021
                                      34 *   VERB FOLLOWED BY ITS OPERANDS.                                      00204021
                                      35 *                                                                       00210021
                                      36 *ENTRY POINTS:                                                          00216021
                                      37 *                                                                       00222021
                                      38 *        PH4                                                            00228021
                                      39 *                                                                       00234021
                                      40 *INPUT:                                                                 00240021
                                      41 *                                                                       00246021
                                      42 *   FILE-3, I-C (P1) TEXT REDUCTION OF PROCEDURE DIVISION.              00252021
                                      43 *                                                                       00258021
                                      44 *OUTPUT:                                                                00264021
                                      45 *                                                                       00270021
                                      46 *  FILE-2, I-C ( P2 ) TEXT TRANSFORMATION OF PROCEDURE DIVISION         00276021
                                      47 *                                                                       00282021
                                      48 *EXTERNAL ROUTINES:                                                     00288021
                                      49 *                                                                       00294021
                                      50 *        COS       LINK TO I-O AND INTERPHASE COMMON REGION             00300021
                                      51 *  (COS IS ALTERNATE NAME FOR PHASE 00 )                                00306021
                                      52 *        PRIME     *              *     PREPARE TABLE                   00312021
                                      53 *        INSERT    *TABLE-HANDLING*     PROVIDE ROOM                    00318021
                                      54 *        TABREL    *              *     RELEASE TABLE                   00324021
                                      55 *                                                                       00330021

                                      59 *EXIT-ERROR-       COMPILER ERROR MSG WHEN IC-TEXT COUNT FIELD = 0,     00354021
                                      60 *                   THEN SKIP TO PHASE 5                                00360021
                                      61 *                                                                       00366021
                                      62 *TABLES/WORK AREAS:                                                     00372021
                                      63 *                                                                       00378021
                                      64 *   ALL EXTENSIVE WORK-AREAS ARE TAMER TABLES, DESCRIBED IN DETAIL      00384021
                                      65 *   AT LOC TAMDEF. SMALL WORK-AREAS START AT LOC DATA.                  00390021
                                      66 *                                                                       00396021
                                      67 *ATTRIBUTES:                                                            00402021
                                      68 *                                                                       00408021
                                      69 *   NOT REUSABLE                                                        00414021
                                      70 *                                                                       00420021
                                      71 *NOTES:                                                                 00426021
                                      72 *                                                                       00432021
                                      73 *   GENERAL ORGANIZATION: 1. VERB ANALYZERS                             00438021
                                      74 *                           A. DATA-MANIPULATION VERBS                  00444021
                                      75 *                           B. PROCEDURE-NAME-HANDLING VERBS            00450021
                                      76 *                           C. ARITHMETIC VERBS, IF, AND ELSE           00456021
                                      77 *                           D. DEBUGGING VERBS                          00462021
                                      78 *                           E. SORT VERBS                               00468021
                                      79 *                           F. COMPILER-DIRECTING VERBS                 00474021
                                      80 *                           G. I-O VERBS                                00480021
                                      81 *                         2. PHASE CONTROLLER                           00486021
                                      82 *                         3. SUBROUTINES                                00492021
                                      83 *                         4. CONSTANTS                                  00498021
                                      84 *                         5. DATA                                       00504021
                                      85 *                         6. INITIALIZATION (OVERLAYS DATA)             00510021
                                      86 *                                                                       00516021
                                      87 *   BASE-REGISTERS FOR 2-6 ARE LOADED DURING INITIALIZATION AND NEV     00522021
                                      88 *      CHANGED.                                                         00528021
                                      89 *   BASE-REGISTER FOR VERB-ANALYZER (RVRB) IS LOADED BY PHASE-CONTR     00534021
                                      90 *      LER EACH TIME A VERB IS FOUND.                                   00540021
                                      91 *   REGISTER 13 IS NOT USED.                                            00546021
                                      92 *   VERB ANALYZERS DO NOT STORE-RESTORE REGISTERS.                      00552021
                                      93 *   ALL PHASE 4 INTERNAL SUBROUTINES SAVE AND RESTORE ALL REGISTERS     00558021
                                      94 *      (EXCEPT FOR THOSE WHICH ADVANCE THE INPUT POINTER RIN).          00564021
                                      95 *      BUT EXTERNAL SUBROUTINE COS CLOBBERS REGISTERS 0 AND 1           00570021
                                      96 *      AND TAMER INSERT ROUTINE MODIFIES REGISTERS 0,2, AND 3.          00576021
                                      97 *      PHASE 4 SUBROUTINES,HOWEVER, WHICH CALL COS AND TAMER DO         00582021
                                      98 *      SAVE  REGISTERS 0 - 3.                                           00588021
                                      99 *                                                                       00594021
1PH40     IKFCBL40                                                                                              PAGE    4
-  LOC  OBJECT CODE    ADDR1 ADDR2  STMT   SOURCE STATEMENT                                       ASM 0201 11.03 02/14/15
0                                    101 *                         5. PHASE INITIALIZATION                       00606021
                                     102 *                         6. DATA                                       00612021
                                     103 *                                                                       00618021
                                     104 *   VERB ANALYZERS ARE GROUPED INTO SEVERAL CSECTS WHICH MAY BE REO     00624021
                                     105 *      GANIZED AT WILL,SINCE EACH VERB HAS ITS OWN BASE. SUBROUTINE     00630021
                                     106 *      CONSTANTS,AND DATA ARE SIMILARLY GROUPED INTO CSECT1 - CSECT     00636021
                                     107 *      WHOSE FIRST LABEL IS, RESPECTIVELY,COMON1 - COMON5. IF REOR-     00642021
                                     108 *      GANIZATION IS NECESSARY, CARE MUST BE TAKEN WITH THESE 5 LAB     00648021
                                     109 *      SINCE IT IS THEIR ADDRESSES THAT GO INTO THE 5 PERMANENT BAS     00654021
                                     110 *      REGISTERS. ALSO, ALL ADCONS SHOULD BE KEPT TOGETHER IN CSECT     00660021
                                     111 *      AND ALL VARIABLE DATA IN CSECT5.                                 00666021
                                     112 *                                                                       00672021
                                     113 *                                                                       00678021
                                     114 *                                                                       00684021
                                     115 *   GENERAL CONSIDERATIONS IN ERROR PROCESSING                          00690021
                                     116 *                                                                       00696021
                                     117 *      ALMOST NO ASSUMPTIONS - 'ERROR RECOVERIES' FOR THE SOURCE PR     00702021
                                     118 *   GRAM - ARE MADE.  OUR HOPE IS TO CHECK AS MUCH AS CAN REASONABL     00708021
                                     119 *   BE CHECKED SO AS TO SAVE REPEATED RECOMPILATIONS. IT IS  N O T      00714021
                                     120 *   TO GUESS WHAT THE PROGRAMMER MAY HAVE INTENDED AND CORRECT HIS      00720021
                                     121 *   MISTAKES.                                                           00726021
                                     122 *      WE PROCESS IN SEQUENCE FORWARD, ALWAYS ASKING 'GIVEN WHAT WE     00732021
                                     123 *   HAVE SO FAR, WHAT IS THE NEXT ELEMENT WE CAN EXPECT?'  WHEN WE      00738021
                                     124 *   FAIL TO FIND IT WE DO NOT GO BACK AND READJUST OUR EXPECTATION.     00744021
                                     125 *   (LIMITED CORE PREVENTS THIS SOPHISTICATION.) WE DELETE.             00750021
                                     126 *      WE ATTEMPT TO CORRECT ONLY IN THE SIMPLEST CASES -- E.G.,        00756021
                                     127 *   UNPAIRED PARENTHESES,MISSING REQUIRED COBOL WORDS WHEN THERE IS     00762021
                                     128 *   NO CHOICE OF OPTIONS.                                               00768021
                                     129 *        IN THE MOST GENERAL TERMS: A WRONG OPERAND WHICH IS ONE OF     00774021
                                     130 *   SERIES (ADD X Y Z TO A) IS DISCARDED. A WRONG OPERAND WHICH IS      00780021
                                     131 *   SINGLE CAUSES THE ENTIRE VERB STATEMENT TO BE DELETED. A WRONG      00786021
                                     132 *   MISSING REQUIRED COBOL WORD IS ASSUMED.AN OPTIONAL CLAUSE CONTA     00792021
                                     133 *   ING WRONG OPERANDS IS DISCARDED.                                    00798021
                                     134 *      WE SEND TO PHASE 5 ONLY CORRECT OUTPUT AS FAR AS WE KNOW. IT     00804021
                                     135 *   CAN BE STUPID BUT SHOULD BE ACCEPTABLE TO THEIR ANALYZERS.          00810021
                                     136 *      WE WRITE NO MESSAGE  IF THE UNWELCOME-UNEXPECTED ELEMENT IS      00816021
                                     137 *   'ERROR-SYMBOL', ASSUMING A PREVIOUS PHASE HAS COMMENTED IT.         00822021
                                     138 *   WE SIMPLY APPEND TO THE OTHER PHASES'S MESSAGE THE ACTION WE AR     00828021
                                     139 *   TAKING, E.G., DELETING STATEMENT,DISCARDING OPTION,ETC.             00834021
                                     140 *      IN A FEW CASES -- NOTABLY THE COMPLEX, POSSIBLY LENGTHY, VER     00840021
                                     141 *   IF AND PERFORM AND THE ARITHMETIC VERBS -- WE SUBSTITUTE ARBITR     00846021
                                     142 *   FOR ILLEGAL OPERANDS. THIS IS MERELY TO FACILITATE OUR CONTINUE     00852021
                                     143 *   PROCESSING AND DOES NOT REPRESENT  AN ATTEMPTED 'CORRECTION'.       00858021
                                     144 *      WE DISCARD MEANINGLESS OPTIONAL WORDS WITHOUT REGARD TO THE      00864021
                                     145 *   INAPPROPRIATENESS OF THEIR USE (E.G., 'IS','ARE','THEN').           00870021
                                     146 *                                                                       00876021
                                     147 *                                                                       00882021

                                     705 *                   V E R B  A N A L Y Z E R S                          02940021
                                     706 *                                                                       02946021
                                     707 *      ALL VERB ANALYZERS START ' USING  *,RVRB '.                      02952021
                                     708 *      THEIR ADDRESSES ARE IN A LIST, ORDERED BY CODE, AT AVRB.         02958021
                                     709 *      IDENT LOADS RVRB FROM THE APPROPRIATE CELL OF THIS LIST, AND     02964021
                                     710 *        TURNS CONTROL OVER TO THE ANALYZER BY A  BCR  UNCOND,RVRB      02970021
                                     711 *                                                                       02976021
                                     712 *      EXIT FROM EACH ANALYZER IS TO IDENT.                             02982021
                                     713 *         BC   UNCOND,IDENT       NORMAL CASE                           02988021
                                     714 *         BC   UNCOND,IDERR       AFTER MSG HAS BEEN WRITTEN            02994021
                                     715 *                                                                       03000021

                                     717 *        THEIR OWN CONVENIENCE.                                         03012021

                                    1914 *******************************************************************     10194021
                                    1915 *                                                                       10200021
                                    1916 *                                                                       10206021
                                    1917 *                            P R F O R M                                10212021
                                    1918 *                                                                       10218021
                                    1919 *                                                                       10224021
                                    1920 *      THE PN USED AS END-OF-RANGE (THE ONE AFTER 'THRU',OR THE ONL     10230021
                                    1921 *       ONE IF THERE IS NO 'THRU')  WAS   GIVEN A PERFORM-BIT IN IT     10236021
                                    1922 *       ATTRIBUTES BY PHASE 1. WHEN PHASE 4 FIRST COMES UPON IT,        10242021
                                    1923 *       WHETHER AS A LHN OR HERE IN THE PERFORM, IT PUTS THIS PN-ID     10248021
                                    1924 *       AND A NEW VN-NUMBER IN THE VNTBL. THIS VN-NUMBER IS THE ONE     10254021
                                    1925 *       REFERRED TO BELOW AS 'RETURN-VN'. IT IS THE SAME ONE ENTERE     10260021
                                    1926 *       IN THE PFMTBL ALONG WITH THE PN-ID OF THE 1ST PN AFTER THE      10266021
                                    1927 *       END-OF-RANGE OF THE PERFORM (THIS PROCESSING IS DONE BY IDE     10272021
                                    1928 *       WHICH PRODUCES THE CODING TO COME BACK AFTER A PERFORM, NAM     10278021
                                    1929 *       'GO VN').                                                       10284021
                                    1930 *                                                                       10290021
                                    1931 *                                                                       10296021
                                    1932 *** STRINGS PRODUCED (OPTIONS 1-3)                                      10302021
                                    1933 *                                                                       10308021
                                    1934 *      OPTION 1. PERFORM PN1 (THRU PN4).                                10314021
                                    1935 *                           MOVE RETURN-VN PFMSAV-N                     10320021
                                    1936 *                           MOVE GN-N RETURN-VN                         10326021
                                    1937 *                           GO PN1                                      10332021
                                    1938 *                      GN-N MOVE PFMSAV-N RETURN-VN                     10338021
                                    1939 *                                                                       10344021
                                    1940 *      OPTION 2. PERFORM PN1 (THRU PN4) X TIMES.                        10350021
                                    1941 *                           MOVE RETURN-VN PFMSAV-N                     10356021
                                    1942 *                           MOVE GN-N RETURN-VN                         10362021
                                    1943 *                           GO-TIMES PN1 X   (SPECIAL GO-VERB)          10368021
                                    1944 *                      GN-N MOVE PFMSAV-N RETURN-VN                     10374021
                                    1945 *                                                                       10380021
                                    1946 *      OPTION 3. PERFORM PN1 (THRU PN4) UNTIL A = B .                   10386021
                                    1947 *                           MOVE RETURN-VN PFMSAV-N                     10392021
                                    1948 *                           MOVE GN-N RETURN-VN                         10398021
                                    1949 *                      GN-N = A B GN-TRUE                               10404021
                                    1950 *                           GO PN1                                      10410021
                                    1951 *                   GN-TRUE MOVE PFMSAV-N RETURN-VN                     10416021
                                    1952 *                                                                       10422021
                                    1953 *                                                                       10428021
                                    1954 *      STRINGS FOR OPTION 4 WITH'VARYING' ARE DETAILED ABOVE THE CO     10434021
                                    1955 *        AT LOC VARY.                                                   10440021
                                    1956 *                                                                       10446021
                                    1957 *                                                                       10452021
                                    1958 *** SUBROUTINES CALLED                                                  10458021
                                    1959 *      GETNXT,GETALL,SAVNXT,STOR45,STLOOP,GENSTR,GENLAB,GENLST,GENG     10464021
                                    1960 *      GENMOV,GNARTH,PUPIR,PUPVNC,PUPLGN,INSERT,PNSRTF,PZSTRT,SRCHT     10470021
                                    1961 *      ISOKSC,ISEND,RDUCOP,OKPFOP,PMKTAL,DECMAX,GETPVN,ERROR            10476021
                                    1962 *                                                                       10482021
                                    1963 *                                                                       10488021
                                    1964 *** ERROR PROCESSING                                                    10494021
                                    1965 *      IF PN DOESNT FOLLOW VERB SKIP WHOLE STATEMENT                    10500021
                                    1966 *      IF PN DOESNT FOLLOW 'THRU' IGNORE 'THRU', CONSIDER STATEMENT     10506021
1PH40     IKFCBL40                                                                                              PAGE   45
-  LOC  OBJECT CODE    ADDR1 ADDR2  STMT   SOURCE STATEMENT                                       ASM 0201 11.03 02/14/15
0                                   1967 *       ENDED                                                           10512021
                                    1968 *      IF PN AFTER 'THRU' IS DEFINED AS PRECEDING PN BEFORE 'THRU',     10518021
                                    1969 *       GIVE WARNING BUT PROCESS NORMALLY                               10524021
                                    1970 *      IF THE 'THRU' PN (OR SINGLE PN) IS ALSO ALTERED PROCESS NORM     10530021
                                    1971 *       WITHOUT MSG. ALTER ANALYZER WILL ISSUE IT AND DELETE THE AL     10536021
                                    1972 *      IF EITHER PN IS IN ILLEGAL SECTION GIVE MSG BUT PROCESS NORM     10542021
                                    1973 *      ASSUME OPTION 1 IF 'VARYING', 'UNTIL', OR OPERAND DOES NOT       10548021
                                    1974 *       FOLLOW LAST PN (LET IDENT WRITE MSG IF IT IS GARBAGE)           10554021
                                    1975 *      ASSUME OPTION 2 IF OPERAND FOLLOWS. IF OPERAND ILLEGAL, SUBS     10560021
                                    1976 *       TUTE 'TALLY'                                                    10566021
                                    1977 *      ASSUME 'TIMES' IF MISSING IN OPTION 2                            10572021
                                    1978 *      ERRORS BETWEEN'UNTIL' AND END-OF-STATEMENT OR 'AFTER' ARE        10578021
                                    1979 *       HANDLED BY THE IF ANALYZER                                      10584021
                                    1980 *      WITHIN OPTION 4, ASSUME 'FROM', 'BY', 'UNTIL' IF MISSING WHE     10590021
                                    1981 *                        EXPECTED                                       10596021
                                    1982 *                       SUBSTITUTE 'TALLY' FOR ILLEGAL OPERANDS         10602021
                                    1983 *                       WARN BUT PROCESS VARIATIONS AFTER 3RD           10608021
                                    1984 *                                                                       10614021
                                    1985 *                                                                       10620021
                                    1986 *** NOTES                                                               10626021
                                    1987 *      PFMSAV-N IS A UNIQUE SAVE-AREA RESERVED BY UPPING THE PSVCTR     10632021
                                    1988 *        COMMON. GN'S ARE  PRODUCED AS NEEDED BY UPPING THE GNCTR.      10638021
                                    1989 *                                                                       10644021
                                    1990 *      FOR ALL OPTIONS, IDENT WILL PRODUCE JUST BEFORE PN2 (OR BEFO     10650021
                                    1991 *        PN5 IF THERE WAS 'THRU PN4')                                   10656021
                                    1992 *                                                                       10662021
                                    1993 *                           GO RETURN-VN                                10668021
                                    1994 *                           EQU RETURN-VN PN2 (OR PN5)                  10674021
                                    1995 *                                                                       10680021
                                    1996 *                                                                       10686021
                                    1997 *                                                                       10692021
                                    1998 *      CONDITIONS FOLLOWING 'UNTIL' ARE EVALUATED BY IF. BEFORE CAL     10698021
                                    1999 *        IF, PRFORM EFFECTIVELY NEGATES THE ENTIRE CONDITION, BECAU     10704021
                                    2000 *        HERE ONE FALLS THRU WHEN THE CONDITION FAILS, WHEREAS IN A     10710021
                                    2001 *        ORDINARY IF-STATEMENT ONE FALLS THRU IF THE CONDITION SUCC     10716021
                                    2002 *                                                                       10722021
                                    2003 *      PERFSW ON DIRECTS IF TO RETURN TO PRFORM RATHER THAN IDENT A     10728021
                                    2004 *        TO ACCEPT 'AFTER' AS A TERMINATOR.                             10734021
                                    2005 *                                                                       10740021
                                    2006 *      VARYSW FOR OPTIONS 1-3 IS USED TO SIGNIFY WHICH OPTION WAS       10746021
                                    2007 *        FOUND IN ORDER TO GENERATE WHATEVER IS SPECIAL TO ANY OPTI     10752021
                                    2008 *        (E.G., THE GO-TIMES VERB, OR THE RETURN-GN PRECEDING A         10758021
                                    2009 *        CONDITION.)                                                    10764021
                                    2010 *                                                                       10770021
                                    2011 *      SORTSW  ON SAYS CALL WAS FROM SORT. NOTHING IS GENERATED AND     10776021

                                    3686 *        CHECKS SYNTAX OF IF STATEMENT,CALLING ON FORMLA TO ANALYZE     20826021
                                    3687 *              EXPRESSIONS                                              20832021
                                    3688 *        CALLS ON PUTSGN AND PUTNIN TO ENTER SIGNS AND OPERANDS IN      20838021
                                    3689 *              THE TABLES AND TO CREATE ARITHMETIC VERB STRINGS         20844021
                                    3690 *        WHEN PARENTHESES ARE FOUND, PUTSGN ADJUSTS THE PTRFLS LABE     20850021
                                    3691 *              TABLE TO REFLECT THE INFLUENCE OF 'NOT' AT THE NEW L     20856021
                                    3692 *        WHEN END,'AND',OR 'OR' IS FOUND,CALLS ON PFINDL TO ENTER T     20862021
                                    3693 *              APPROPRIATE BY-PASS LABELS IN THE PSHTBL PUSH-DOWN T     20868021
                                    3694 *              AND TO GENERATE THE APPROPRIATE FALL-THRU LABELS         20874021
                                    3695 *                                                                       20880021
                                    3696 *        IN GENERAL, 'BYPASS LABEL' IS THE BRANCH TAKEN WHEN A GIVE     20886021
                                    3697 *              CONDITION FAILS, 'FALL-THRU LABEL' WHEN IT IS SUCCES     20892021
                                    3698 *              FUL                                                      20898021
                                    3699 *                                                                       20904021
                                    3700 *                                                                       20910021
                                    3701 *        SYNTAX IS CHECKED BY THE FOLLOWING ALGORITHM                   20916021
                                    3702 *                                                                       20922021
                                    3703 *  IS IT                YES                             NO              20928021
                                    3704 *                                                                       20934021
                                    3705 *  1. 'NOT'    PROCESS,GETNXT,GO TO 2        GO TO 2                    20940021
                                    3706 *  2. (        PROCESS,GETNXT,GO TO 1        GO TO 3                    20946021
                                    3707 *  3. ALPHALIT PROCESS,GETNXT GO TO R1       GO TO 4                    20952021
                                    3708 *  4. FORMULA  GO TO 5                       E R R O R - - - - - -      20958021
                                    3709 *  5. ONLY DN  GO TO R2 (CLASS TEST)         GO TO 6                    20964021
                                    3710 *  6. ONLY NUM GO TO R5 (RELATION TEST)      GO TO R3 (SIGN TEST)       20970021
                                    3711 *                                                                       20976021

                                    3713 *                                                                       20988021
                                    3714 * R1. LEV. 88  PROCESS ALL,GETNXT,GO TO R4   GO TO R5                   20994021

                                    3717 * R4. )        PROCESS,GETNXT,GO TO R4       TURN ON PNDREL, GO TO      21012021

                                    3777 *        THE SWITCHES PNDREL AND PRTURN ARE USED FOR HANDLING IMPLI     21372021
                                    3778 *          SUBJECTS AND RELATIONALS.                                    21378021
                                    3779 *              PNDREL IS TURNED ON WHENEVER AN IMPLIED SUBJECT WOUL     21384021
                                    3780 *                ILLEGAL, THAT IS, AT THE BEGINNING OF THE STATEMEN     21390021
                                    3781 *                AND AFTER A CONDITIONAL VARIABLE,SIGN TEST,OR CLAS     21396021
                                    3782 *                TEST IS FOUND. IT IS TURNED OFF WHEN A RELATIONAL      21402021
                                    3783 *                IS FOUND. IF PNDREL IS ON AND NO RELATIONAL IS FOU     21408021
                                    3784 *                IT IS AN ERROR.                                        21414021

                                    3786 *                OFF. THEN THE PROGRAM BRANCHES DIRECTLY TO SEEK A      21426021

                                    3788 *                ON,PROCESSING OF THE LEFT-HAND TERM IS INHIBITED.      21438021

                                    5089 *** STRINGS PRODUCED                                                    29244021
                                    5090 *      A SEGMENTED CONTINUOUS STRING IS PRODUCED FOR THE SORT-FILE,     29250021
                                    5091 *       SORT KEYS, AND 'USING' AND/OR 'GIVING' (EITHER OR BOTH OF       29256021
                                    5092 *       THESE IS REPLACED BY SPACE-HOLDER 'ZERO' IF ABSENT). AFTER      29262021
                                    5093 *       STRING, WHOSE LAST ELEMENT IS 'END', COMES -- IF THERE IS I     29268021
                                    5094 *       PROCEDURE -- A PERFORM STRING FOR THE SECTION NAME. THEN A      29274021
                                    5095 *       1-ELEMENT STRING 'SORT 'END''.  THEN IF THERE IS OUTPUT PRO     29280021

                                    5097 *       'END''                                                          29292021
                                    5098 *                                                                       29298021

                                    5100 *                                    DESC        DESC         USING     29310021
                                    5101 *                                                                       29316021
                                    5102 *                   ZERO   'END                                         29322021
                                    5103 *                   GIVING                                              29328021
                                    5104 *      (WITH SORT VERB REPEATED AFTER EVERY 4 ELEMENTS)                 29334021
                                    5105 *                                                                       29340021
                                    5106 *  THEN IF INPUT PROCEDURE                                              29346021
                                    5107 *                   MOVE-4 VN1 PFMSAV1                                  29352021
                                    5108 *                   MOVE-4 GN1 VN1                                      29358021
                                    5109 *                   GO  SN1                                             29364021

                                    5115 *                   MOVE-4 GN2 VN2                                      29400021
                                    5116 *                   GO  SN2                                             29406021

                                    6950 *       VERB FINALLY DETERMINED. IT IS SET TO 0 AT THE START OF THE     40410021
                                    6951 *       ANALYZER,AND AT THE END IF NO VALID STATEMENT WAS FOUND. EA     40416021
                                    6952 *       OPTIONAL WORD FOUND CAUSES A TENTATIVE VERB-CODE TO BE STOR     40422021

                                    6954 *       A 1 IS PUT IN THE LOW-ORDER BIT. THIS PRODUCES THE END-OF-U     40434021
                                    6955 *       VERB WHICH IS GENERATED BY IDENT WHEN IT FINDS THAT A DECLA     40440021
                                    6956 *       TIVE SECTION HAS ENDED. BEGINNING-USE VERBS ARE EVEN, END-U     40446021

                                    8417 *                          VERBS RETURN TO IDENT AFTER PROCESSING T     49212021

                                    8420 *                          TION.                                        49230021

                                    8646 *                                                                       50586021
                                    8647 *                                                                       50592021
                                    8648 *** NOTES                                                               50598021
                                    8649 *      PHASE 1 SETS A BIT IN THE ATTRIBUTES OF EVERY PN FOR EACH OF     50604021
                                    8650 *        THE FOLLOWING CONDITIONS                                       50610021
                                    8651 *                                                                       50616021
                                    8652 *        IT IS A SECTION NAME                                           50622021
                                    8653 *        IT IS ALTERED                                                  50628021
                                    8654 *        IT PRECEDES A SIMPLE GO STATEMENT                              50634021
                                    8655 *        IT PRECEDES AN EXIT STATEMENT                                  50640021
                                    8656 *        IT IS THE END-OF-RANGE OF A PERFORM                            50646021
                                    8657 *        IT IS REFERENCED BY *DEBUG                                     50652021
                                    8658 *        IT IS DEFINED UNDER *DEBUG                                     50658021
                                    8659 *        IT IS A DUMMY CREATED BY PHASE 1                               50664021
                                    8660 *                                                                       50670021
                                    8661 *      ALTER,PERFORM BITS ON AN LHN CAUSE AN ENTRY TO BE MADE IN VN     50676021
                                    8662 *      PERFORM BIT CAUSES ID OF  N E X T  PN TO GO INTO PFMTBL          50682021
                                    8663 *      DEBUG-REFERENCE BIT CAUSES THE PN, ITS RPD NUMBER, AND A GN      50688021
                                    8664 *        GO INTO DBGTBL AND 'CALL GN' TO BE GENERATED                   50694021
                                    8665 *      IF PHASE 1 FOUND A 'READY TRACE' ANYWHERE IN THE PROCEDURE       50700021
                                    8666 *        DIVISION, IT TURNED ON A SWITCH IN COMMON.  IF THIS SWITCH     50706021
                                    8667 *        IS ON PHASE 4 GENERATES A TRACE VERB AFTER EVERY LHN EXCEP     50712021
                                    8668 *        DUMMIES                                                        50718021
                                    8669 *      SECTION NAMES INCLUDE AMONG THEIR ATTRIBUTES THEIR RPD NUMBE     50724021
                                    8670 *        AND THE ID OF THE FOLLOWING SECTION.  THESE ARE SAVED ALON     50730021
                                    8671 *        WITH THE SN'S OWN ID TO ALLOW CHECKING LEGALITY OF PROCEDU     50736021
                                    8672 *        BRANCHING STATEMENTS                                           50742021
                                    8673 *      FIRST 2 BYTES OF ATTRIBUTES ARE ZEROED ON EXIT FROM IDLHN UN     50748021
                                    8674 *        GO OR EXIT BIT IS ON.  THUS ATTRIBUTES TELL GO AND EXIT        50754021
                                    8675 *        ANALYZERS THAT A PN DID OR DID NOT IMMEDIATELY PRECEDE THE     50760021
                                    8676 *        VERB                                                           50766021
                                    8677 *                                                                       50772021

0                                   8950 *=2    GETNXT    READ ROUTINE                                           52410021
                                    8951 *******************************************************************     52416021
                                    8952 *                                                                       52422021
                                    8953 *                        G E T N X T                                    52428021
                                    8954 *                                                                       52434021
                                    8955 *      BAL     RCS,GETNXT                                               52440021
                                    8956 *      (RETURN)                                                         52446021
                                    8957 *                                                                       52452021
                                    8958 *                                                                       52458021
                                    8959 *      COPIES 'NOISE' ON OUTPUT FILE, GETS ANOTHER ENTITY               52464021
                                    8960 *      STORES SEQUENCE NUMBER AT NXTCRD,THEN GETS ANOTHER               52470021
                                    8961 *      UPDATES RIN TO POINT TO NEXT SIGNIFICANT ENTRY                   52476021
                                    8962 *      COMPUTES BYTCNT, TOTAL NUMBER OF BYTES IN ENTITY WHOSE ADDRE     52482021
                                    8963 *        IS STORED AT PNTIN                                             52488021
                                    8964 *      MOVES FIRST HALF-WORD OF THIS ENTITY TO GOTTEN                   52494021
                                    8965 *                                                                       52500021
                                    8966 *                                                                       52506021
                                    8967 *      (IF NEXTIN SW IS ON, TURNS IT OFF, MOVES NXTWRD TO GOTTEN,MO     52512021
                                    8968 *       NXTCNT TO BYTCNT, MOVES GOTTEN TO ITS ORIGINAL PLACE IN         52518021
                                    8969 *       INPUT BUFFER, AND EXITS)                                        52524021
                                    8970 *                                                                       52530021
                                    8971 *      N O T E .  THERE ARE 2 POINTERS AND 2 BYTE COUNTERS.             52536021
                                    8972 *                                                                       52542021
                                    8973 *      RIN AND BYTCNT ARE REFERENCED BY MOST ROUTINES AND MAY           52548021
                                    8974 *       OCCASIONALLY BE CHANGED BY THEM IF THEY WISH TEMPORARILY TO     52554021
                                    8975 *       PRETEND INPUT IS SOMEWHERE ELSE THAN IN THE BUFFER, E.G., A     52560021
                                    8976 *       CURENT.                                                         52566021
                                    8977 *                                                                       52572021
                                    8978 *       TRUPNT AND TRUCNT ALWAYS REFER TO THE TRUE INPUT BUFFER.        52578021
                                    8979 *       GETNXT ALWAYS RESETS RIN AND BYTCNT TO THE VALUE OF TRUPNT      52584021
                                    8980 *       AND TRUCNT.                                                     52590021
                                    8981 *                                                                       52596021
                                    8982 *** SUBROUTINES CALLED                                                  52602021
                                    8983 *      COS,GENCRD,COPYIN                                                52608021
                                    8984 *                                                                       52614021
                                    8985 *                                                                       52620021
                                    8986 *******************************************************************     52626021

                                   10046 *      ROUTINE TO SEARCH FOR A GIVEN PROCEDURE-NAME ID IN ANY OF TH     58986021
                                   10047 *        PROCEDURE-NAME TAMER TABLES (VNTBL,PFMTBL,DBGTBL).             58992021

                                   10053 *      (RETURN ID NOT IN TABLE)                                         59028021
                                   10054 *      (RETURN ID FOUND IN TABLE)                                       59034021
                                   10055 *                                                                       59040021
                                   10056 *      BEFORE CALLING SRCHTA, CALLER MUST STORE WANTED P-N ID AT        59046021
                                   10057 *        SRCHNM.                                                        59052021
                                   10058 *                                                                       59058021
                                   10059 *      IF THE P-N ID IS FOUND AND THE TABLE SEARCHED IS                 59064021
                                   10060 *        VNTBL OR                                                       59070021
                                   10061 *        PFMTBL - THE VNNUMBER FOLLOWING THE P-N ID IN THE TABLE IS     59076021
                                   10062 *                      STORED AT VNNUM                                  59082021
                                   10063 *        DBGTBL - THE GN NUMBER FOLLOWING THE P-N ID IN THE TABLE I     59088021
                                   10064 *                      STORED AT VNNUM AND THE RPD NUMBER AT DBGRPD     59094021
                                   10065 *                            THEN THE ENTRY IS ZEROED TO PREVENT RE     59100021
                                   10066 *                                                                       59106021

                                   10068 *        AT TABADR                                                      59118021
                                   10069 *                                                                       59124021

                                   10072 *        OF-RANGE OF A PERFORM.  THE 2ND IS A UNIQUE VN-NUMBER ASSO     59142021
                                   10073 *        TED WITH THIS PN.                                              59148021
                                   10074 *                                                                       59154021
                                   10075 *      PFMTBL CONSISTS OF DOUBLE 2-BYTE ENTRIES. THE 1ST OF EACH PA     59160021
                                   10076 *        IS THE ID OF THE PROCEDURE NAME FOLLOWING THE END-OF-RANGE     59166021
                                   10077 *        OF A PERFORM. THE 2ND IS THE VN NUMBER CORRESPONDING TO TH     59172021

                                   10705 *      GETNXT,SAVNXT,SAVCUR,COUNT,PNSRTF,ISINTG,ERROR                   62940021
                                   10706 *                                                                       62946021
                                   10707 *                                                                       62952021
                                   10708 *** ERROR PROCESSING                                                    62958021
                                   10709 *      ANY ERROR FOUND CAUSES INPUT (AT CURENT) TO BE REPLACED BY       62964021
                                   10710 *        ERROR-SYMBOL AND MODE BY 0. VERB ANALYZERS WILL THEN TREAT     62970021
                                   10711 *        THE INCORRECTLY SUBSCRIPTED NAME AS A LEPER.                   62976021
                                   10712 *      A SUBSCRIPT GROUP IS CONSIDERED TO START ONLY IF ( FOLLOWS       62982021
                                   10713 *        THE DATA NAME AND TO END AT THE FIRST NON-OPERAND (OPERAND     62988021
                                   10714 *        INCLUDES DATA OPERANDS,NON-DATA OPERANDS, AND ERROR SYMBOL     62994021
                                   10715 *      ERRORS DIAGNOSED ARE                                             63000021
                                   10716 *              INCORRECT NUMBER OF SUBSCRIPTS                           63006021
                                   10717 *              NON-NUMERIC SUBSCRIPT                                    63012021
                                   10718 *              NON-INTEGER SUBSCRIPT                                    63018021
                                   10719 *              SUBSCRIPT WHICH ITSELF SHOULD BE SUBSCRIPTED             63024021
                                   10720 *              INCORRECT TERMINATOR                                     63030021
                                   10721 *                                                                       63036021
                                   10722 *                                                                       63042021
                                   10723 *** NOTES                                                               63048021
                                   10724 *      DECIDES WHETHER DATA-NAME IS SUBSCRIPTED.IF NOT,EXITS.           63054021
                                   10725 *      IF SO,FOR ALL CASES EXCEPT MOVE-,ADD-,SUBTRACT-CORRESPONDING     63060021
                                   10726 *       PUTS INTO THE SUBSCRIPT-DEFINING TABLE FOR CORRECTLY WRITTE     63066021
                                   10727 *       SUBSCRIPTED VARIABLES,THE FOLLOWING STRING.                     63072021
                                   10728 *                   SSVERB    (EL.COUNT=2+NO. OF SUBSCRIPTS)            63078021
                                   10729 *                   DATA-NAME    (SUBSCRIPTED VARIABLE)                 63084021
                                   10730 *                   DN OR NUMLIT (SUBSCRIPT 1)                          63090021
                                   10731 *                   DN OR NUMLIT (SUBSCRIPT 2 IF PRESENT)               63096021
                                   10732 *                   DN OR NUMLIT (SUBSCRIPT 3 IF PRESENT)               63102021
                                   10733 *                   SSID         (SAME AS DATA-NAME ABOVE,BUT WITH      63108021
                                   10734 *                                  HEADER OF 31 INSTEAD OF 30,AND W     63114021
                                   10735 *                                  A 2-BYTE BINARY UNIQUE IDENTIFIE     63120021
                                   10736 *                                 REPLACING ADDRESSING PARAMETERS)      63126021
                                   10737 *       SUBSTITUTES THE SSID FOR THE ORIGINAL DATA-NAME IN 'INPUT',     63132021
                                   10738 *       WHICH,THROUGH SAVCUR ROUTINE,IS DESIGNATED AS BEING AT LOC.     63138021
                                   10739 *       CURENT.                                                         63144021
                                   10740 *                                                                       63150021
                                   10741 *     WHEN VERB ANALYZERS CREATE THEIR STRINGS, THEY USE THE SSID       63156021
                                   10742 *       INSTEAD OF THE ORIGINAL INPUT.                                  63162021
                                   10743 *                                                                       63168021
                                   10744 *      GENSTR GENERATES ENTIRE CONTENTS OF SUBSCRIPT-DEFINING TABLE     63174021
                                   10745 *     DEFSBS, B E F O R E  CONTENTS OF STRING TABLE.                    63180021
                                   10746 *                                                                       63186021
                                   10747 *      IDENT REINITIALIZES (EMPTIES) DEFSBS.                            63192021
1PH40     IKFCBL40                                                                                              PAGE  225
-  LOC  OBJECT CODE    ADDR1 ADDR2  STMT   SOURCE STATEMENT                                       ASM 0201 11.03 02/14/15
0                                  10748 *      VERB ANALYZERS WHICH NEED TO SAVE THE SUBSCRIPT-DEFINING STR     63198021
                                   10749 *       FOR A RE-USABLE OPERAND-1 (EG.,'MOVE SUBSCRIPTED-VARIABLE T     63204021
                                   10750 *       X,Y,Z ... IF SUBSCRIPTED-VARIABLE = X OR Y AND Z') SAVE DIS     63210021
                                   10751 *       GIVEN BY THE SUBSCR ROUTINE, AT LEFTSS AND REINITIALIZE DEF     63216021
                                   10752 *       AS NEEDED.                                                      63222021
                                   10753 *                                                                       63228021
                                   10754 *                                                                       63234021
                                   10755 *      IF ANY ERROR IN SUBSCRIPTING IS FOUND,NOTHING IS PUT IN DEFS     63240021
                                   10756 *       AND ERROR-SYMBOL IS SUBSTITUTED FOR THE DATA-NAME IN 'CUREN     63246021
                                   10757 *       RDUCOP REJECTS THIS AS AN OPERAND.                              63252021
                                   10758 *                                                                       63258021
                                   10759 *                             **********                                63264021
                                   10760 *                                                                       63270021
                                   10761 *      MOVE-, ADD-, SUBTRACT-CORRESPONDING REQUIRE SPECIAL HANDLING     63276021
                                   10762 *       SINCE PHASE-3 SENDS ON THE SOURCE-PROGRAM FORM TO PHASE 4 F     63282021
                                   10763 *       SYNTAX ANALYSIS,BUT NO STRINGS CAN BE GENERATED FROM THIS.      63288021
                                   10764 *       THEN IT SENDS THE CORRESPONDING-SERIES EXPANSIONS BUT WITHO     63294021
                                   10765 *       INCLUDING THEIR SUBSCRIPTS.                                     63300021
                                   10766 *                                                                       63306021
                                   10767 *      WHEN THE 3  ANALYZERS FIND THE WORD 'CORRESPONDING' IMMEDIAT     63312021
                                   10768 *       AFTER THE VERB, THEY TURN ON DRYRUN SWITCH, INDICATING SYNT     63318021
                                   10769 *       CHECK BUT NO STRING PRODUCTION. WHEN THEY ARE ABOUT TO EXIT     63324021
                                   10770 *       IDENT AND DRYRUN IS ON, THEY TURN IT OFF AND TURN ON CORRSW     63330021
                                   10771 *       INDICATING THAT WHAT FOLLOWS IS PHASE-3 EXPANSION. THE NEXT     63336021
                                   10772 *     OCCURRENCE OF THE WORD'CORRESPONDING' INDICATES THE END OF        63342021
                                   10773 *       PHASE-3 EXPANSIONS.                                             63348021
                                   10774 *                                                                       63354021
                                   10775 *      EACH ANALYZER BEFORE CALLING RDUCOP,STORES AT LOC. THISOP TH     63360021
                                   10776 *       ADDRESS OF EITHER LOC. OPRND1 OR LOC. OPRND2, ACCORDING TO      63366021
                                   10777 *       WHICH OF ITS OPERANDS IT IS PROCESSING.                         63372021
                                   10778 *                                                                       63378021
                                   10779 *      DURING A 'DRY-RUN' SUBSCR, INSTEAD OF PUTTING A SUBSCRIPT-DE     63384021
                                   10780 *       ING STRING IN DEFSBS, SIMPLY PRESERVES THE SUBSCRIPTS THEM-     63390021
                                   10781 *       SELVES AT WHICHEVER LOC. THISOP INDICATES. THE ANALYZERS NO     63396021
                                   10782 *       FOR THEMSELVES WHETHER,DURING DRY-RUN, OPERAND-1,OPERAND-2,     63402021
                                   10783 *       BOTH WERE SUBSCRIPTED.                                          63408021
                                   10784 *                                                                       63414021
                                   10785 *      ON THE NEXT TIME THRU, WHEN CORRSW IS ON, THEY TURN ON OPSSS     63420021
                                   10786 *       IF THE RESPECTIVE OPERAND WAS SHOWN TO BE SUBSCRIPTED DURIN     63426021
                                   10787 *       THE DRY-RUN.  NOW SUBSCR, FINDING OPSSSW ON,GETS THE SUBSCR     63432021
                                   10788 *       FOR THE OPERANDS CREATED BY PHASE-3 FROM THE LOC. INDICATED     63438021
                                   10789 *       BY THISOP (RATHER THAN FROM THE INPUT STREAM AS IN ORDINARY     63444021
                                   10790 *       CASES).IT THEN CREATES THE SUBSCRIPT-DEFINING STRING FOR EA     63450021
                                   10791 *       OF THESE IN TURN AND SUBSTITUTES AN SSID FOR EACH OPERAND       63456021
                                   10792 *       SENT AS PHASE-3 CORRESPONDING-EXPANSION.                        63462021
                                   10793 *                                                                       63468021
                                   10794 *******************************************************************     63474021

                                   12274 *=2            IF-COMPUTE ROUTINES                                      72354021
                                   12275 *******************************************************************     72360021
                                   12276 *                                                                       72366021
                                   12277 *                                                                       72372021
                                   12278 *                             P F I N D L                               72378021
                                   12279 *                                                                       72384021
                                   12280 *      BAL     RCS,PFINDL                                               72390021
                                   12281 *      (RETURN)                                                         72396021
                                   12282 *                                                                       72402021
                                   12283 *      CALLED BY IF                                                     72408021
                                   12284 *      EXAMINES PTRFLS FROM THE ENTRY AT PTRFLS+PLOW THRU THE ENTRY     72414021
                                   12285 *        AT PTRFLS+HILEV. (IF HAS SET PLOW TO REFLECT FALL-THRU OR      72420021
                                   12286 *        BYPASS SIDE OF TABLE AND THE TYPE OF TERMINATOR -- 'OR',       72426021
                                   12287 *        'AND', OR END.)                                                72432021
                                   12288 *                                                                       72438021
                                   12289 *** SUBROUTINES CALLED                                                  72444021
                                   12290 *      PUPLGN,INSERT,PACKTB                                             72450021
                                   12291 *                                                                       72456021
                                   12292 *                                                                       72462021
                                   12293 *** NOTES                                                               72468021
                                   12294 *  THE EFFECTIVE ADDRESS CALCULATED FROM PLOW IS                        72474021
                                   12295 *          START-OF-TABLE + PARENTHESIS-LEVEL * 5 +                     72480021
                                   12296 *                                                                       72486021
                                   12297 *      3  ON BYPASS, 1  ON FALL-THRU BRANCH FOR 'END'                   72492021
                                   12298 *      3             6                          'AND'                   72498021
                                   12299 *      1             3                          'OR'                    72504021
                                   12300 *      6             8                          'NOT AND'               72510021
                                   12301 *      3             6                          'NOT OR'                72516021
                                   12302 *                                                                       72522021
                                   12303 *                                                                       72528021
                                   12304 *        FOR BYPASS-BRANCHES,  THE 1ST NON-ZERO PTRFLS LABEL FOUND      72534021
                                   12305 *      IS LOCATED IN OR  ENTERED INTO PSHTBL AND GIVEN A MASTER-BIT     72540021
                                   12306 *      (INDICATING THAT ALL LABELS FOLLOWING IT IN PSHTBL UP TO THE     72546021
                                   12307 *      NEXT MASTER ARE EQU'D TO IT).  MOVES THIS LABEL TO PTRFLS +      72552021
                                   12308 *      PLOW + PRNLEV.  SEARCHES PSHTBL FOR ALL NON-ZERO LABELS          72558021
                                   12309 *      FOUND AT HIGHER PTRFLS LEVELS, REMOVES THEIR MASTER BITS AND     72564021
                                   12310 *      MOVES THEM AND NON-MASTERS FOLLOWING THEM ADJACENT TO THE NE     72570021
                                   12311 *      MASTER. ZEROES ALL PTRFLS LABELS PROCESSED EXCEPT THE NOW NE     72576021
                                   12312 *      MASTER.                                                          72582021
                                   12313 *                                                                       72588021
                                   12314 *        FOR FALL-THRU LABELS, GENERATES AS LGN'S ALL LABELS FOUND      72594021
                                   12315 *      PTRFLS AT OR AFTER PTRFLS + PLOW + PRNLEV. SEARCHES PSHTBL       72600021
                                   12316 *      FOR THESE LABELS,GENERATES ALL NON-MASTERS FOLLOWING UP TO N     72606021
                                   12317 *      MASTER IN PSHTBL.  ZEROES GENERATED LABELS FROM PTRFLS AND       72612021
                                   12318 *      PSHTBL.  AT EXIT CLOSES PSHTBL TO ELIMINATE ZEROED GAPS.         72618021
                                   12319 *                                                                       72624021
                                   12320 *      IF NO LABEL IS FOUND IN PTRFLS,AND FALL-THRU BRANCH IS SOUGH     72630021
                                   12321 *        JUST EXITS. IF BYPASS BRANCH IS SOUGHT,UPDATES LGN AND STO     72636021
                                   12322 *        IT AS A MASTER IN PTRFLS AND PSHTBL                            72642021
1PH40     IKFCBL40                                                                                              PAGE  257
-  LOC  OBJECT CODE    ADDR1 ADDR2  STMT   SOURCE STATEMENT                                       ASM 0201 11.03 02/14/15
0                                  12323 *                                                                       72648021
                                   12324 *      ON EXIT, BYPASS BRANCH IDENTIFIER IS IN DISPL. OF RGN            72654021
                                   12325 *                                                                       72660021
                                   12326 *                                                                       72666021
                                   12327 *      THIS PROCESS INSURES THAT THERE ARE NO DUPLICATIONS IN PSHTB     72672021
                                   12328 *      AND THAT NO MASTER IS EQU'D TO ANOTHER MASTER. WHEN LABELS A     72678021
                                   12329 *      MOVED FROM PSHTBL ('FIRST-IN-LAST-OUT'), NO FURTHER ANALYSIS     72684021

0                                  12524 *=2    FORMLA    REDUCTION OF ARITHMETIC EXPRESSIONS                    73854021
                                   12525 *******************************************************************     73860021
                                   12526 *                                                                       73866021
                                   12527 *                                                                       73872021
                                   12528 *                             F O R M L A                               73878021
                                   12529 *                                                                       73884021
                                   12530 *        BAL   RCS,FORMLA                                               73890021
                                   12531 *        (RETURN ERROR OR NOT FORMULA)                                  73896021
                                   12532 *        (RETURN SINGLE NON-NUMERIC DATA-OPERAND)                       73902021
                                   12533 *        (RETURN VALID FORMULA)                                         73908021
                                   12534 *                                                                       73914021
                                   12535 *        ROUTINE IS CALLED BY COMPUTE,IF,ON,UNTIL,TO ANALYZE AND        73920021
                                   12536 *         EVALUATE FORMULAS.                                            73926021
                                   12537 *                                                                       73932021
                                   12538 *        'FORMULA' HERE MEANS SINGLE OPERAND,OR SEVERAL OPERANDS OR     73938021
                                   12539 *         FORMULAS,SEPARATED BY OPERATORS (+,-,*,/,**)                  73944021
                                   12540 *        'OPERAND' HERE MEANS DATA-NAME OR NUMERIC OR FLOATING LITE     73950021
                                   12541 *         SURROUNDED AT OPTION BY PARENS AND PRECEDED AT OPTION BY      73956021
                                   12542 *         UNARY MINUS.                                                  73962021
                                   12543 *                       OUTLINE OF SYNTAX ANALYSIS                      73968021
                                   12544 *        IS ENTITY         .  YES                       .  NO           73974021
                                   12545 *                          .                            .               73980021
                                   12546 *     2  -                 .  PROCESS,GET NEXT,GO TO 4. .GO TO 4        73986021
                                   12547 *     4  (                 .  PROCESS,GET NEXT,GO TO 2. .GO TO 6        73992021
                                   12548 *     6  DATA-NAME OR LIT  .  PROCESS,GET NEXT,GO TO 8. .EXIT,ERR.O     73998021
                                   12549 *     8  )                 .  PROCESS,GET NEXT,GO TO 8. .GO TO 10       74004021
                                   12550 *     10 OPERATOR          .  PROCESS,GET NEXT,GO TO 4. .EXIT,FINIS     74010021
                                   12551 *                                                                       74016021
                                   12552 *                                                                       74022021
                                   12553 *** SUBROUTINES CALLED                                                  74028021
                                   12554 *      GETNXT,PUTSGN,PUTNIN,PEMPTY,PMKTAL,DECMAX                        74034021
                                   12555 *                                                                       74040021
                                   12556 *        CALLS ON  PUTNIN TO ENTER OPERAND  IN NOUNS TABLE              74046021
                                   12557 *                  PUTSGN TO ENTER OPERATOR IN SIGNS TABLE AND TO       74052021
                                   12558 *                    DECIDE THE MOMENT TO CREATE A VERB STRING AND      74058021
                                   12559 *                    DELETE FROM SIGNS AND NOUNS TABLE                  74064021
                                   12560 *                 PEMPTY,AT END OF FORMULA, TO CREATE ALL REMAINING     74070021
                                   12561 *                    STRINGS AND EMPTY THE TABLES                       74076021
                                   12562 *                                                                       74082021
                                   12563 *** NOTES                                                               74088021
                                   12564 *      DMAXSW IS A 2-BYTE SWITCH WHICH = 0 WHEN THE PART OF AN EXPR     74094021
                                   12565 *       SION BEING PROCESSED IS NOT PART OF AN EXPONENT OR DIVISOR.     74100021
                                   12566 *       WHEN / OR ** IS FOUND AND IT = 0, IT IS SET TO PRNLEV+5, OT     74106021
                                   12567 *      WISE LEFT ALONE. WHEN +,-,OR * IS FOUND AND DMAXSW IS NOT        74112021
                                   12568 *       LOWER THAN PRNLEV+5 IT IS SET BACK TO 0, OTHERWISE LEFT ALO     74118021
                                   12569 *       WHEN DMAXSW IS NOT 0, DECMAX IS NOT CALLED FOR AN OPERAND.      74124021
                                   12570 *       THUS NO PART OF A PARENTHESIZED DIVISOR OR EXPONENT PARTICI     74130021
                                   12571 *       PATES IN THE CALCULATION OF DMAX.                               74136021
                                   12572 *                                                                       74142021
                                   12573 *                                                                       74148021
                                   12574 *                                                                       74154021
                                   12575 *      IF ANY NUMERIC OPERAND AT ALL WAS FOUND PFNDOP SWITCH IS ON.     74160021
                                   12576 *        AT EXIT 1 CALLING ROUTINE MAY NEED TO TEST PFNDOP FOR          74166021
                                   12577 *        ERROR CONDITIONS.  EXIT 2 REPRESENTS ERROR FOR COMPUTE BUT     74172021
                                   12578 *        NOT FOR IF.                                                    74178021
1PH40     IKFCBL40                                                                                              PAGE  262
-  LOC  OBJECT CODE    ADDR1 ADDR2  STMT   SOURCE STATEMENT                                       ASM 0201 11.03 02/14/15
0                                  12579 *        AT EXIT 3 THE CONTROL-BYTE OF PRSULT SHOWS WHETHER THIS        74184021
                                   12580 *        WAS A TRUE MULTI-OPERAND FORMULA ( RESULT IS AN IR),  A        74190021
                                   12581 *        SINGLE DATA-NAME, OR A SINGLE NUMERIC LITERAL.                 74196021
                                   12582 *                                                                       74202021
                                   12583 *                                                                       74208021
                                   12584 *      IN CASE FORMLA FINDS A NON-NUMERIC OPERAND AFTER FINDING         74214021

                                   13495 *                                                                       79680021
                                   13496 *** NOTES                                                               79686021
                                   13497 *          PARAMETER LIST HAS THE FOLLOWING FORM                        79692021

                                   13500 *      .                                                                79710021
                                   13501 *      .                                                                79716021
                                   13502 *      DC      AL3(PARAM)                                               79722021
                                   13503 *        WHERE   MM IS MESSAGE NUMBER                                   79728021
                                   13504 *                 S    SEVERITY CODE                                    79734021
                                   13505 *                 N    NUMBER OF PARAMETERS                             79740021
                                   13506 *                 Z    CONCLUSION NUMBER FOR UNDEFINED                  79746021
                                   13507 *                 P    CONCLUSION PARAMETER POINTER FOR UNDEFINED       79752021
                                   13508 *                                                                       79758021
                                   13509 *        IF THE ADDRESS OF A PARAMETER IS 0, ERROR WILL TAKE IT AS      79764021
                                   13510 *          CURRENT INPUT, I.E., THE ADDRESS CONTAINED IN PNTIN.         79770021
                                   13511 *                                                                       79776021
                                   13512 *       IF THE ADDRESS OF A PARAMETER IS 1, ERROR WILL TAKE ITS REA     79782021
                                   13513 *         ADDRESS TO BE IN RA0.                                         79788021
                                   13514 *                                                                       79794021
                                   13515 *        IF THE ADDRESS OF A PARAMETER IS 2, ERROR WILL INTERPRET I     79800021
                                   13516 *         AS THE VERB FOR THE CURRENT STATEMENT.                        79806021
                                   13517 *                                                                       79812021
                                   13518 *        IF THE ADDRESS OF A PARAMETER IS 3,4, OR 5, ERROR WILL TAK     79818021
                                   13519 *          IT AS THE MODE OF AN OPERAND AND PICK IT UP FROM LOC. MO     79824021
                                   13520 *          MODEL, OR MODER, RESPECTIVELY.                               79830021
                                   13521 *                                                                       79836021
                                   13522 *        SOME MESSAGES HAVE NO PARAMETERS                               79842021
                                   13523 *                                                                       79848021
                                   13524 *                                                                       79854021
                                   13525 *      WHEN ANY OF THE PARAMETERS IS ERROR-SYMBOL (INDICATING AN UN     79860021
                                   13526 *       SOLVABLE OPERAND FOUND IN A PREVIOUS PHASE), PHASE 4 DOES N     79866021
                                   13527 *       WRITE A MESSAGE BUT MERELY APPENDS ONE OF SEVERAL STANDARD      79872021
                                   13528 *       CLUSIONS TO THE PREVIOUS PHASE'S MESSAGE. IF THE CONCLUSION     79878021
                                   13529 *       ITSELF HAS PARAMETERS, P TELLS HOW MANY TO SKIP OVER TO GET     79884021
                                   13530 *       TO THE WANTED ONE. IF THE QTH PARAMETER IS WANTED IN A MESS     79890021
                                   13531 *       HAVING N PARAMETERS, THEN P = N + 1 - Q.                        79896021
                                   13532 *        4 OR ONE OF ITS PREDECESSORS HAD ALREADY WRITTEN A MESSAGE     79902021
                                   13533 *                                                                       79908021
                                   13534 *      ENTRANCE AT ERONCE CAUSES MSGSW TO BE TESTED. IF IT IS ON, N     79914021
                                   13535 *        MESSAGE IS WRITTEN. IF IT IS OFF IT IS TURNED ON AND A MES     79920021

                                   13540 *      ENTRANCE AT ERRIF FROM IF ANALYZER.  CERTAIN MESSAGES SHOULD     79950021

                                   13544 *                                                                       79974021
                                   13545 *      THE FORM OF A PHASE-4 ERROR MESSAGE IS                           79980021
                                   13546 *                                                                       79986021
                                   13547 *              00 06 00 MMMM CCCC S4                                    79992021
                                   13548 *              00 0N XX XX ...                                          79998021

                                   13555 *              MMMM IS 2-BYTE MESSAGE NUMBER                            80040021
                                   13556 *              XXXX AND YYYY ARE PARAMETERS IN INTERNAL TEXT            80046021
                                   13557 *              Z IS CONCLUSION NUMBER                                   80052021
                                   13558 *      CONCLUSIONS ARE - 1  ASSUMED                                     80058021
                                   13559 *                        2  IGNORED                                     80064021
                                   13560 *                        3  DISCARDED                                   80070021
                                   13561 *                        4  TEST DISCARDED                              80076021

                                   13566 *                        9  SUBSTITUTING --                             80106021
                                   13567 *                        A  SUBSTITUTING FIRST OCCURRENCE OF --         80112021
                                   13568 *                        B  STATEMENT ACCEPTED AS WRITTEN               80118021
                                   13569 *                        C  SYSTEM UNIT ASSUMED                         80124021

                                   13571 *                              CODING                                   80136021
